 <p>Flexbox is a total of a new set of css hat allows people who are designers to make sure create flexible layouts. The responsive design has dramatically changed for the last couple of years because browser support flexbox has great resources. These days web designers use CSS properties like css declaration for example display:block, or display:flexbox, this made designers so easy to control what they are doing. CSS flexbox is a css layout that promotes responsive designed to allow elements within a container to automatically adjust depending on different sizes. There are also many execution of the flexbox syntaxs. As the text says “The CSS layout mechanism lets us arrange elements in a truly web-like way. Some elements can be fixed, while others scroll. The order in which they appear can be independent of the source order”. The most important flexbox that have a lot of cool stuff and its part future layout. Browser support for flexbox is excellent tools and majority of designers prefer browser support instead of safari browsers. The flexbox layout is the future because it is so much easier and maintainable with flexboxes. It is developed primarily to avoid overflowing parent element. It will fill the space expanding child elements. “Flexbox's properties involve a whole array of control over alignment and ordering, and once you get used to how it works, it starts to become clear how little CSS you actually have to write to augment how we're building things today”.
